103
00:10:48.408 --> 00:10:52.407
The Running Man,
America's favorite game show.

104
00:10:55.450 --> 00:11:00.158
A child, your child, happy, loving, caring...

105
00:11:00.242 --> 00:11:03.616
Can you believe this shit?
Twenty-four hours a day.

106
00:11:03.908 --> 00:11:06.449
- Seven days a week.
- Don't listen to it.

107
00:11:06.533 --> 00:11:10.241
I worry about the kids.
The network shuts down the schools.

108
00:11:10.325 --> 00:11:12.991
The kids are either in hiding
or getting basic training,

109
00:11:13.075 --> 00:11:15.116
brainwashed by the TV.

110
00:11:15.200 --> 00:11:18.116
We can jam the network
once we find the uplink to the satellite.

111
00:11:18.200 --> 00:11:20.074
Then we'll broadcast the truth.

112
00:11:20.159 --> 00:11:23.074
Truth? Hasn't been very popular lately.

113
00:11:23.491 --> 00:11:26.241
Can't find the code or the uplink.

114
00:11:26.325 --> 00:11:30.574
Don't know where the network
hid something that big, but they managed.

115
00:11:31.159 --> 00:11:33.365
Stevie, would you mind?

116
00:11:35.742 --> 00:11:37.991
Goodbye, my lovely.

117
00:11:51.285 --> 00:11:54.491
You're one of the cops
who locked up all my friends,

118
00:11:54.576 --> 00:11:56.075
burned my songs.

119
00:11:56.160 --> 00:11:59.326
People like you took this country
and turned it into a jail.

120
00:11:59.409 --> 00:12:01.825
- We don't want his death on our hands.
- He's a cop.

121
00:12:01.909 --> 00:12:04.867
- He's the Butcher of Bakersfield.
- Come on, Mic.

122
00:12:04.951 --> 00:12:07.491
You can see through that crap.
It's network propaganda.

123
00:12:07.576 --> 00:12:08.617
We don't know that.

124
00:12:08.701 --> 00:12:10.408
We know we wouldn't be here
if he hadn't helped us.

125
00:12:10.492 --> 00:12:12.742
We also know he's not one of us.

126
00:12:12.826 --> 00:12:15.117
Perhaps now he's seen too much.

127
00:12:16.076 --> 00:12:17.658
I've seen too much?

128
00:12:17.743 --> 00:12:19.450
All I've seen is a bunch of low foreheads

129
00:12:19.534 --> 00:12:22.159
who think they can change the world
with dreams and talk.

130
00:12:22.243 --> 00:12:23.950
It's too late for that.

131
00:12:24.035 --> 00:12:27.366
If you're not ready to act,
give me a break and shut up.

132
00:12:32.201 --> 00:12:34.742
Nothing worth losing
your head over, though, huh?

133
00:12:38.035 --> 00:12:39.408
You got it.

134
00:12:44.743 --> 00:12:45.992
Hey, get out of here.

135
00:13:04.827 --> 00:13:07.951
Well, there's your ride. It's all set.

136
00:13:08.577 --> 00:13:10.576
Nothing like first class.

137
00:13:11.744 --> 00:13:13.327
Seńorita, seńorita. You want to come in?

138
00:13:13.410 --> 00:13:15.367
Yeah. Hey, you, too?

139
00:13:16.077 --> 00:13:17.659
I guess this is it.

140
00:13:17.744 --> 00:13:20.492
Now you, Weiss,
stay out of the National Database, okay?

141
00:13:20.577 --> 00:13:24.701
And you, Laughlin, stop trying to teach
the constitution to the street punks.

142
00:13:24.785 --> 00:13:28.035
- See you guys at the 10-year prison reunion.
- You can still join us if you want to.

143
00:13:28.119 --> 00:13:30.534
No, thank you.
My brother's going to get me out of the city.

144
00:13:30.619 --> 00:13:33.492
Plus, I'm not into politics. I'm into survival.

145
00:13:33.577 --> 00:13:35.576
Nowadays, Fritz, it's the same thing.

146
00:13:35.660 --> 00:13:38.327
Laughlin, save it for the written test.
Good luck.

147
00:13:38.410 --> 00:13:39.993
Yeah, for all of us.

148
00:14:31.078 --> 00:14:33.036
We need you, Damon!

149
00:14:36.369 --> 00:14:40.036
Brenda, do you have this week's ratings,
or do I have to guess?

150
00:14:40.287 --> 00:14:43.660
They're the same as last week,
and those were the same all last month.

151
00:14:43.745 --> 00:14:46.827
I guess we've just peaked.
But it's not like we've dropped.

152
00:14:46.911 --> 00:14:48.910
Not likely. You're beautiful, sweetheart.

153
00:14:50.287 --> 00:14:51.910
- Sorry, Mr. Killian!
- Hey, that's all right.

154
00:14:51.995 --> 00:14:53.535
- What's your name?
- Dan.

155
00:14:53.620 --> 00:14:55.827
Dan, you're doing good work.
Looks beautiful. Don't worry.

156
00:14:55.911 --> 00:14:57.077
- Thank you.
- Okay?

157
00:14:57.162 --> 00:14:58.535
Thank you.

158
00:14:59.661 --> 00:15:02.452
Brenda, if that asshole
is mopping the floor tomorrow,

159
00:15:02.536 --> 00:15:05.827
you'll be mopping it
for the rest of the week. Let's go!

160
00:15:46.579 --> 00:15:48.578
Security code accepted.

161
00:16:11.121 --> 00:16:12.745
Edward?

162
00:16:14.454 --> 00:16:17.369
Damon, were you down in wardrobe yet?
They've got your new jackets.

163
00:16:17.454 --> 00:16:20.369
- They're fantastic!
- Who chose the colors?

164
00:16:20.746 --> 00:16:23.661
- Hey, how are my people today?
- Fine, sir. Thank you.

165
00:16:23.746 --> 00:16:26.536
You're looking good. Love that...
Tony! Tony!

166
00:16:26.621 --> 00:16:28.329
- What have you got for me?
- Damon, thank God.

167
00:16:28.412 --> 00:16:30.120
The Justice Department's been calling
every 10 minutes.

168
00:16:30.204 --> 00:16:33.662
Just give them an evasive answer.
Tell them to go fuck themselves.

169
00:16:33.747 --> 00:16:35.370
You got my coffee?

170
00:16:35.747 --> 00:16:38.412
- I want to know what we got, all right?
- All right. Let's see.

171
00:16:42.663 --> 00:16:44.121
Lights.

172
00:16:47.872 --> 00:16:50.912
Oh, God. Kitchen, toast and coffee.

173
00:16:51.913 --> 00:16:53.662
ICS Channel One.

174
00:16:57.997 --> 00:17:01.829
Are you ready for pain?
Are you ready for suffering?

175
00:17:02.039 --> 00:17:04.204
If the answer is yes,

176
00:17:04.289 --> 00:17:07.621
then you're ready
for Captain Freedom's Workout.

177
00:17:07.705 --> 00:17:11.163
Yes, it's America's own Captain Freedom,

178
00:17:11.247 --> 00:17:15.579
10-time national champion,
the greatest stalker to ever play the game.

179
00:17:15.663 --> 00:17:19.163
All right, now, all you runners,
ready, get set, go!

180
00:17:19.247 --> 00:17:22.495
We interrupt Captain Freedom's Workout
to bring you this urgent news bulletin.

181
00:17:22.580 --> 00:17:25.121
The city police are engaged
in a door-to-door search

182
00:17:25.205 --> 00:17:28.829
for Benjamin A. Richards,
known as the Butcher of Bakersfield.

183
00:17:29.413 --> 00:17:33.163
Richards, a former police officer,
was the helicopter pilot

184
00:17:33.247 --> 00:17:34.996
who went berserk 18 months ago,

185
00:17:35.080 --> 00:17:39.038
firing without warning
on a crowd of innocent civilians.

186
00:17:39.122 --> 00:17:43.079
If you see this man, do not approach him.
Contact your local block warden.

187
00:17:43.164 --> 00:17:45.662
He is considered armed and dangerous.

188
00:17:45.747 --> 00:17:47.663
Don't make a sound, you understand?

189
00:17:47.748 --> 00:17:50.331
Who are you? A friend of my brother's?

190
00:17:53.623 --> 00:17:56.164
- What are you talking about?
- This is his apartment.

191
00:17:56.248 --> 00:17:57.830
I moved in last month.

192
00:17:57.914 --> 00:18:00.788
They told me the last tenant
was taken away for...

193
00:18:00.873 --> 00:18:03.289
- Yes?
- For re-education.

194
00:18:06.414 --> 00:18:07.747
Help!

195
00:18:10.372 --> 00:18:12.080
El asesino is in my house!

196
00:18:12.248 --> 00:18:14.788
El Butcher of Bakersfield's in my bathroom!

197
00:18:14.873 --> 00:18:17.747
That's the ticket. No pain, no gain.

198
00:18:17.831 --> 00:18:21.205
Let go of me! Let me go! Let go!

199
00:18:21.539 --> 00:18:24.413
Now, listen to me,
because I'm only going to say this once.

200
00:18:24.497 --> 00:18:27.997
This is all a lie. I was framed.
I'm completely innocent.

201
00:18:28.081 --> 00:18:31.247
- Yeah, sure.
- Now, be quiet and stay still.

202
00:18:31.331 --> 00:18:33.538
I'm out of here in five minutes.

203
00:18:37.081 --> 00:18:39.830
Hi, this is Amber. I'm not home right now.

204
00:18:39.914 --> 00:18:44.164
I'm out somewhere having a wonderful time
with glamorous people in a fabulous place.

205
00:18:44.248 --> 00:18:48.331
So, when you hear the tone, control
your jealousy and leave your message.

206
00:18:50.623 --> 00:18:51.622
"Baby Face" March.

207
00:18:51.706 --> 00:18:53.705
Are you kidding me? Next.

208
00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:56.747
How's this one? Case 114. Schoolteacher.

209
00:18:56.832 --> 00:19:00.163
Killed his wife and his mother-in-law
at a faculty dinner party with a steak knife.

210
00:19:00.248 --> 00:19:02.206
Yeah. See I like that quality.

211
00:19:02.707 --> 00:19:05.748
He's the sort that the neighbors say,
"Such a quiet man,

212
00:19:05.833 --> 00:19:08.832
"but never too busy to say hello."
But look at him.

213
00:19:08.916 --> 00:19:12.415
He weighs 120 pounds.
He wouldn't last 30 seconds.

214
00:19:13.207 --> 00:19:14.540
Who else?

215
00:19:15.207 --> 00:19:18.498
What about those bank robbers?
The ones who made that suicide pact.

216
00:19:18.582 --> 00:19:21.957
- Did they commit suicide?
- Obviously not, Damon.

217
00:19:22.416 --> 00:19:23.915
Then they're unreliable.

218
00:19:23.999 --> 00:19:25.248
I got a friend at a talent agency.

219
00:19:25.332 --> 00:19:27.082
Maybe they've got an ax-murderer
or something.

220
00:19:27.165 --> 00:19:31.415
- Hello, gorgeous.
- Somebody with stamina.

221
00:19:31.499 --> 00:19:33.540
Tony. Tony.

222
00:19:34.999 --> 00:19:38.832
Pipe that feed in here now!
Take a look at this.

223
00:19:39.290 --> 00:19:42.456
This is yesterday's prison break. Hey. Look!

224
00:19:43.249 --> 00:19:47.415
Look at that mother move, huh?
Is he beautiful? Who is he?

225
00:19:47.499 --> 00:19:49.623
Are you kidding? That's Ben Richards.

226
00:19:49.707 --> 00:19:52.832
The cop from the massacre? Sensational.

227
00:19:52.916 --> 00:19:56.040
- Perfect contestant. I want him!
- You can't have him.

228
00:19:56.124 --> 00:19:57.164
Why not?

229
00:19:57.249 --> 00:20:00.124
Damon, you know our contract.
We never get military prisoners.

230
00:20:00.207 --> 00:20:02.957
Who's a military prisoner?
He's still at large.

231
00:20:03.041 --> 00:20:05.206
Yeah? Well, they'll get him for me.

232
00:20:05.290 --> 00:20:07.415
Cadres can't have it both ways.

233
00:20:07.999 --> 00:20:11.373
They want ratings.
I can get 10 points for his biceps alone.

234
00:20:11.457 --> 00:20:13.415
Hello. Yeah, this is Killian.

235
00:20:13.499 --> 00:20:16.791
Get me the Justice Department,
Entertainment Division.

236
00:20:16.875 --> 00:20:21.833
No, hold that.
Operator, get me the President's agent.

237
00:20:24.084 --> 00:20:25.541
What is this?

238
00:20:26.042 --> 00:20:29.041
That's my synthesizer setup. I'm a musician.

239
00:20:31.250 --> 00:20:34.707
Well, I'm really a singer.
I write music for the network.

240
